.TH KRYON 1
.SH NAME
kryon \- Kryon language compiler
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B kryon
[
.B -o
.I output
]
[
.B -h
]
.I input.kry
.SH DESCRIPTION
.I Kryon
is a declarative UI language for building Inferno applications.
It compiles
.I .kry
source files into Limbo
.I .b
source files, which can then be compiled with
.IR limbo (1)
to produce Dis executables.
.PP
The Kryon language provides a simple, intuitive syntax for defining
user interfaces using widgets similar to Tk, with support for
reactive properties, event handlers, and automatic layout management.
.PP
The compiler takes a Kryon source file and generates equivalent
Limbo code that uses the Tk and wmclient libraries to create
the specified user interface.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.B -o \fIoutput\fP
Specify the output file name.
If not provided, the output file name is derived from the input
file name by replacing the
.B .kry
extension with
.BR .b .
.TP
.B -h
Print a usage message and exit.
.SH EXAMPLES
Compile a Kryon source file to Limbo:
.EX
kryon hello.kry
.EE
.PP
Compile with specific output name:
.EX
kryon -o myapp.b hello.kry
.EE
.PP
Compile and then build the Dis executable:
.EX
kryon hello.kry && limbo hello.b
.EE
.SH LANGUAGE OVERVIEW
A Kryon source file defines a single Window containing a hierarchy
of widgets. The basic structure is:
.PP
.EX
Window {
    title = "My Application"
    width = 400
    height = 300
    bg = "#191919"

    // Widgets go here
    Label {
        text = "Hello, World!"
        fg = "white"
    }
}
.EE
.PP
For complete language documentation, see
.IR kryon (7).
.SH WIDGETS
Kryon provides the following built-in widgets:
.TP
.B Button
Clickable button with text label.
.TP
.B Canvas
Drawing area for custom graphics.
.TP
.B Checkbutton
Checkbox with on/off state.
.TP
.B Column
Vertical container for child widgets.
.TP
.B Entry
Single-line text input field.
.TP
.B Frame
Generic container with border options.
.TP
.B Img
Image display widget.
.TP
.B Label
Text display widget.
.TP
.B Listbox
Scrollable list of items.
.TP
.B Menubutton
Dropdown menu button.
.TP
.B Message
Multi-line text display.
.TP
.B Radiobutton
Radio button for exclusive selection groups.
.TP
.B Row
Horizontal container for child widgets.
.TP
.B Scale
Slider for numeric value selection.
.SH FILES
.TF /dis/kryon.dis
.TP
.B /dis/kryon.dis
The Kryon compiler executable.
.TP
.B /appl/cmd/kryon/kryon.b
Compiler source code.
.TP
.B /appl/kryon/
Example Kryon applications.
.SH SOURCE
.B /appl/cmd/kryon
.SH "SEE ALSO"
.IR limbo (1),
.IR wm (1),
.IR tk (2),
.IR kryon (7)
.SH BUGS
Error messages report line numbers from the generated Limbo code
rather than the original Kryon source when compilation fails
in the second stage.
